headline: MedeAnalytics Appoints Justin L. Neece as Chief Growth Officer
summary: MedeAnalytics, a leading provider of healthcare data management and analytics solutions, today announced the appointment of Justin L. Neece as Chief Growth Officer. With more than three decades of leadership in healthcare technology and operational strategy, Neece brings a proven track record of leading transformative initiatives, expanding market reach, and delivering quantifiable impact across the healthcare ecosystem.

headline: Dollar Tree Posts Better-Than-Expected Earnings. Why the Stock Is Falling.
summary: Dollar Tree  posted an earnings beat and strong results for the fiscal second quarter, but the stock was falling following an underwhelming third-quarter forecast.  Adjusted earnings in the second quarter of 77 cents a share topped the consensus estimate of 42 cents.  Dollar Tree  hiked its fiscal-year net sales guidance to a range of $19.3 billion to $19.5 billion, up from $18.5 billion to $19.1 billion.
